Package Attributes

Class AttributeValueList

  • java.lang.Object
    • Attributes.AttributeValueList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AttributeValueList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is a list of Attribute-DataObject-Operator triples. In particular, one can use this list to check for two lists whether the first list implies the other list.
    See Also:

      • implies

        public boolean implies​(AttributeValueList other,
                       Context context)
        checks for every attribute-value in 'this' and 'other', whether 'value operator otherValue' holds, where the operator is taken from 'other'.
        Example:
        this = age 20
        other = age 30,LESS
        yields true because 20 LESS 30 is true.
        Attributes occurring only in 'other' are ignored.
        Parameters:
        other - another list
        Returns:
        the result of the comparison.
